Contributing to geex

Thank you for helping to make geex better!

Bug reports

If you think you have found a bug in geex, please submit an issue here. Include:

  • a brief description of the problem
  • a minimal, complete, and verifiable example of the problem
  • the version(s) of geex and the version(s) of R that are giving the trouble

Feature requests

Do you have an idea that could make geex more user-friendly, more accurate, faster, or better in some way? Let us know by submitting an issue.

If you have already developed the feature, before submitting a pull request, please submit an issue first.

Conduct

If you have any doubts that your behavior as a contributor may not meet our code of conduct, then please review our code of conduct.
